---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
import '../styles/enhancements.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
    <script type="application/ld+json">
      {"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https://yarova.ca/#org","name":"Yarova","url":"https://yarova.ca","description":"Canadian IT workplace simulation and placement. Operating since 2018.","foundingDate":"2018-09-01","address":{"@type":"PostalAddress","addressLocality":"Langley","addressRegion":"BC","addressCountry":"CA"}},{"@type":"Course","name":"Yarova Simulated Work Experience","description":"Simulated remote workplace for DevOps and SRE engineers. Real squad, real Team Lead, real tickets. Full support from resume to probation. $1,500 flat.","provider":{"@id":"https://yarova.ca/#org"},"offers":{"@type":"Offer","price":"1500","priceCurrency":"CAD","availability":"https://schema.org/LimitedAvailability"}}]}
    </script>
  </head>
  <body data-screen-label="Yarova simwork home">
    <a class="skip" href="#main">Skip to content</a>

    <Header />

    <!-- Reading preferences (ND-friendly) -->
    <div class="prefs" id="prefs">
      <button class="prefs-toggle" id="prefsToggle" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="prefsPanel">Reading preferences</button>
      <div class="prefs-panel" id="prefsPanel" role="dialog" aria-label="Reading preferences">
        <h4>Reading preferences</h4>
        <p class="hint">Adjust the page to suit your reading style.</p>
        <div class="pref-row">
          <div>
            <div class="label">Wider spacing</div>
            <div class="desc">More breathing room between sections.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="switch" data-mode="spacious" role="switch" tabindex="0" aria-checked="false"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pref-row">
          <div>
            <div class="label">Larger text</div>
            <div class="desc">Bump body text by ~15%.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="switch" data-mode="larger" role="switch" tabindex="0" aria-checked="false"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <main id="main">

      <!-- HERO -->
      <section id="hero" class="hero" data-screen-label="01 Hero">
        <div class="hero-glow"></div>
        <div class="container">
          <div class="hero-eyebrow">
            <span>Real-job simulation &middot; Canada &middot; DevOps &amp; SRE</span>
            <span class="tag">Open now &middot; 5 seats</span>
          </div>
          <h1 class="r-up">Stop Applying<br />with a Blank Resume.<br /><span class="acc">Get Real-Job Experience Today.</span></h1>
          <p class="hero-sub r-up d1">The closest thing to your first day on the job. Without the first-day anxiety.<br />Real squad. Real Team Lead. Real daily standups. Real tickets. Full support &mdash; resume to probation.</p>
          <div class="hero-actions r-up d2">
            <a href="https://cal.com/yarova-fxqeea/discovery-call" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-cal-link="yarova-fxqeea/discovery-call" data-cal-namespace="discovery-call" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}' class="btn btn-amber btn-lg magnetic">Book a discovery call <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
            <a href="#routine" class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg">See how it works <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
          </div>
          <p class="trust-anchor r-up d2">$1,500 flat &middot; No upsells &middot; Re-enroll free until placed &middot; Canada only</p>
          <div class="placement-stream r-up d3" aria-label="Recent placements">
            <span class="stream-label">Recent placements &rarr;</span>
            <div class="stream-track">
              <div class="stream-inner">
                <span class="chip">SRE &middot; Toronto &middot; $108K</span>
                <span class="chip">DevOps &middot; Vancouver &middot; $96K</span>
                <span class="chip">Senior SRE &middot; Ottawa &middot; $142K</span>
                <span class="chip">Platform Eng &middot; Mississauga &middot; $118K</span>
                <span class="chip">DevOps &middot; Victoria &middot; $88K</span>
                <span class="chip">DevSecOps &middot; Calgary &middot; $84K</span>
                <span class="chip">SRE &middot; Toronto &middot; $108K</span>
                <span class="chip">DevOps &middot; Vancouver &middot; $96K</span>
                <span class="chip">Senior SRE &middot; Ottawa &middot; $142K</span>
                <span class="chip">Platform Eng &middot; Mississauga &middot; $118K</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-meta r-up d3">
            <div class="cell"><span class="k">Engineers placed</span><span class="v"><span data-count="370">0</span><small>since 2018</small></span></div>
            <div class="cell"><span class="k">Placed within 6 months</span><span class="v"><span data-count="91" data-suffix="%">0</span><small>of engineers enrolled</small></span></div>
            <div class="cell"><span class="k">Program fee</span><span class="v"><span data-count="1500" data-prefix="$">$0</span><small>CAD &middot; flat &middot; one-time</small></span></div>
            <div class="cell"><span class="k">Guarantee</span><span class="v">Until placed<small>re-enroll free</small></span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- PROBLEM -->
      <section id="problem" class="section alt" data-screen-label="02 Problem">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="sec-strip">
            <span class="num">01 / 07</span><span class="dot"></span><span>The problem</span><span class="dot"></span><span>1 min read</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="r-up">You&rsquo;re not failing.<br /><em>The system is broken.</em></h2>
          <p class="lead r-up d1" style="margin-top: 24px;">Every morning you open your laptop and send another application into silence. Another automated rejection. Another day wondering what you&rsquo;re doing wrong. You&rsquo;re not doing anything wrong. The Canadian tech job market has a structural trap &mdash; and it catches almost everyone without local team experience.</p>

          <div class="catch22 r-up d2">
            <div class="c22-step">
              <span class="n">01</span>
              <div>
                <div class="t">No local experience</div>
                <div class="d">Hiring managers skip your application. They want someone who has already worked inside a Canadian engineering team.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="c22-arrow">&darr;</div>
            <div class="c22-step">
              <span class="n">02</span>
              <div>
                <div class="t">No job offer</div>
                <div class="d">You can&rsquo;t get the experience because no company will hire you to give you the chance.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="c22-arrow">&darr;</div>
            <div class="c22-step locked">
              <span class="n">03</span>
              <div>
                <div class="t">More certificates don&rsquo;t fix this</div>
                <div class="d">Hiring managers see right through tutorial projects. They hire people who already know how to work inside a real team.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="shame-box r-up d3">
            <p>&ldquo;Your brain is not broken. The system is.&rdquo;</p>
            <span>Step inside. We&rsquo;ve got you.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- TRACKS -->
      <section id="tracks" class="section" data-screen-label="03 Tracks">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="sec-strip">
            <span class="num">02 / 07</span><span class="dot"></span><span>Two tracks</span><span class="dot"></span><span>Pick the role you want to be hired into</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="r-up">Choose the squad<br /><em>you want to work in.</em></h2>
          <p class="lead r-up d1" style="margin-top: 24px;">Two tracks. One Team Lead. Pick the role you want to be hired into &mdash; then work it for 3 months like a real employee.</p>

          <div class="track-grid r-up d2">
            <div class="track-card">
              <div class="tc-badge">Track 1</div>
              <h3>DevOps &amp; DevSecOps</h3>
              <p class="tc-role">You build and maintain the infrastructure that lets developers ship code safely and fast.</p>
              <div class="tc-daily">
                <div class="tc-label">Your daily work</div>
                <ul>
                  <li>Build automated CI/CD pipelines</li>
                  <li>Manage cloud infrastructure and networking</li>
                  <li>Fix security vulnerabilities in containers and pipelines</li>
                  <li>Write and review Terraform and Kubernetes manifests</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="tc-tools">
                <div class="tc-label">Tools you use</div>
                <div class="tc-chips">
                  <span>AWS</span><span>Terraform</span><span>GitHub Actions</span><span>Kubernetes</span><span>Docker</span><span>Snyk</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="tc-schedule">
                <span class="tc-label">Batch schedule</span>
                <span>3 months &middot; Morning standup slot</span>
              </div>
              <a href="https://cal.com/yarova-fxqeea/discovery-call" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-cal-link="yarova-fxqeea/discovery-call" data-cal-namespace="discovery-call" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}' class="btn btn-amber tc-cta">Join this track <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
            </div>

            <div class="track-card">
              <div class="tc-badge">Track 2</div>
              <h3>SRE &mdash; Site Reliability Engineering</h3>
              <p class="tc-role">You keep the production systems alive. When something breaks, your squad fixes it.</p>
              <div class="tc-daily">
                <div class="tc-label">Your daily work</div>
                <ul>
                  <li>Monitor live application health dashboards</li>
                  <li>Respond to and resolve simulated incidents</li>
                  <li>Write runbooks and post-mortem reports</li>
                  <li>Build and tune alerting and SLO configurations</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="tc-tools">
                <div class="tc-label">Tools you use</div>
                <div class="tc-chips">
                  <span>AWS</span><span>Kubernetes</span><span>Prometheus</span><span>Grafana</span><span>PagerDuty</span><span>Datadog</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="tc-schedule">
                <span class="tc-label">Batch schedule</span>
                <span>3 months &middot; Afternoon standup slot</span>
              </div>
              <a href="https://cal.com/yarova-fxqeea/discovery-call" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-cal-link="yarova-fxqeea/discovery-call" data-cal-namespace="discovery-call" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}' class="btn btn-amber tc-cta">Join this track <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="tracks-note">Not sure which track to pick? The discovery call is 30 minutes. We&rsquo;ll help you decide based on your background and target roles.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ROUTINE -->
      <section id="routine" class="section alt" data-screen-label="04 Routine">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="sec-strip">
            <span class="num">03 / 07</span><span class="dot"></span><span>How it works</span><span class="dot"></span><span>Real job format</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="r-up">This is not a course.<br /><em>It runs like a real remote job.</em></h2>
          <p class="lead r-up d1" style="margin-top: 24px;">You do not study alone. You do not watch videos. From day one, you log into a live squad environment every morning. Here is what your week looks like.</p>

          <div class="routine-steps r-up d2">
            <div class="routine-step">
              <div class="rs-num">01</div>
              <div class="rs-body">
                <h3>Morning standup &mdash; every weekday</h3>
                <p>Your whole squad joins a live group call. You say what you finished yesterday, what you&rsquo;re building today, and where you&rsquo;re stuck. Your Team Lead unblocks you. Fifteen minutes. Done.</p>
                <div class="rs-detail">Group call &middot; Whole squad &middot; Every weekday &middot; 15 min</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="routine-step">
              <div class="rs-num">02</div>
              <div class="rs-body">
                <h3>Ticket board &mdash; real tasks, pulled daily</h3>
                <p>You log into the project board and pull your next task. It looks exactly like a real corporate Jira ticket: acceptance criteria, a definition of done, and a peer reviewer assigned. You build it. You submit it.</p>
                <div class="rs-detail">Real ticket format &middot; One task at a time &middot; Async completion</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="routine-step">
              <div class="rs-num">03</div>
              <div class="rs-body">
                <h3>Team Lead review &mdash; every submission</h3>
                <p>Your Team Lead reviews every piece of work you submit &mdash; async, on GitHub, line by line. Comments land in your pull request. You address them. You merge. The ticket closes.</p>
                <div class="rs-detail">Async code review &middot; GitHub PRs &middot; Every submission</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="result-box r-up d3">
            <div class="rb-label">The result</div>
            <div class="rb-text">Every ticket you merge is a real resume bullet.<br />Every merged PR is a real GitHub contribution.<br />By the time you interview, you show the work &mdash; you don&rsquo;t describe it.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- SUPPORT CALLS -->
      <section id="support" class="section" data-screen-label="05 Support">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="sec-strip">
            <span class="num">04 / 07</span><span class="dot"></span><span>Support calls</span><span class="dot"></span><span>You&rsquo;re never alone</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="r-up">We&rsquo;re in your corner.<br /><em>All the way to probation.</em></h2>
          <p class="lead r-up d1" style="margin-top: 24px;">The squad work gives you the experience. These calls carry you through the job hunt &mdash; resume, interviews, background checks, and the first 90 days of your new role. All bookable. All 1:1. All included in the $1,500.</p>

          <div class="support-grid r-up d2">
            <div class="support-card">
              <div class="sc-icon">&#9998;</div>
              <h3>Resume review</h3>
              <p>We take your actual ticket history from the squad and write your resume line by line. Every bullet point is a real task you shipped &mdash; not a tutorial project.</p>
              <div class="sc-meta">
                <span>45 min &middot; 1:1</span>
                <span>Anytime &mdash; your choice</span>
              </div>
              <a href="https://cal.com/yarova-fxqeea/resume-review" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-cal-link="yarova-fxqeea/resume-review" data-cal-namespace="resume-review" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}' class="btn btn-ghost sc-btn">Book this call <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
            </div>

            <div class="support-card">
              <div class="sc-icon">&#128172;</div>
              <h3>Interview prep</h3>
              <p>You book an interview. We connect before it. We run the exact questions that company uses, in the format they use them. Every interview you book gets its own prep session.</p>
              <div class="sc-meta">
                <span>45 min &middot; 1:1</span>
                <span>Before each interview</span>
              </div>
              <a href="https://cal.com/yarova-fxqeea/interview-prep" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-cal-link="yarova-fxqeea/interview-prep" data-cal-namespace="interview-prep" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}' class="btn btn-ghost sc-btn">Book this call <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
            </div>

            <div class="support-card">
              <div class="sc-icon">&#128274;</div>
              <h3>Background check prep</h3>
              <p>We help you structure your portfolio, references, and project documentation so your background check passes cleanly. We tell you exactly how to list the squad work on your resume without misrepresentation.</p>
              <div class="sc-meta">
                <span>30 min &middot; 1:1</span>
                <span>When your offer arrives</span>
              </div>
              <a href="https://cal.com/yarova-fxqeea/bg-check-prep" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-cal-link="yarova-fxqeea/bg-check-prep" data-cal-namespace="bg-check-prep" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}' class="btn btn-ghost sc-btn">Book this call <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
            </div>

            <div class="support-card">
              <div class="sc-icon">&#127758;</div>
              <h3>Day-1 prep</h3>
              <p>The day before you start your new job. We run through what to expect, what to ask, what to listen for, and what to avoid in your first week. So you walk in ready &mdash; not guessing.</p>
              <div class="sc-meta">
                <span>30 min &middot; 1:1</span>
                <span>Day before your start date</span>
              </div>
              <a href="https://cal.com/yarova-fxqeea/day-one-prep" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-cal-link="yarova-fxqeea/day-one-prep" data-cal-namespace="day-one-prep" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}' class="btn btn-ghost sc-btn">Book this call <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
            </div>

            <div class="support-card">
              <div class="sc-icon">&#128200;</div>
              <h3>Probation check-ins</h3>
              <p>At 30, 60, and 90 days into your new role. We check how it&rsquo;s going, help you navigate anything that feels unclear, and confirm you&rsquo;re on track to clear probation safely.</p>
              <div class="sc-meta">
                <span>20 min &middot; 1:1</span>
                <span>30 / 60 / 90 days in</span>
              </div>
              <a href="https://cal.com/yarova-fxqeea/probation-checkin" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-cal-link="yarova-fxqeea/probation-checkin" data-cal-namespace="probation-checkin" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}' class="btn btn-ghost sc-btn">Book this call <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- TESTIMONIALS -->
      <section class="section alt" data-screen-label="06 Voices">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="sec-strip">
            <span class="num">05 / 07</span><span class="dot"></span><span>What engineers say</span><span class="dot"></span><span>Three voices &middot; all Canadian roles</span>
          </div>
          <h2>What the engineers who went through it say.</h2>

          <div class="testis">
            <div class="testi">
              <div class="quote">CS degree and 80 rejections. Eight months into Yarova, three offers. Every interviewer opened my GitHub before the call &mdash; the merged PRs did the talking.</div>
              <div class="meta-row"><span><b>DevOps track</b></span><span>8 months</span><span class="achievement">$102k base</span></div>
              <div class="who"><div class="avatar" style="background:#1F3A5F;">PA</div><div><div class="name">Priya A.</div><div class="role">SRE &middot; fintech, Toronto</div></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="testi">
              <div class="quote">Background-check stage usually breaks me. Yarova handled the references, the verification, the offer-letter line review. I showed up and said yes.</div>
              <div class="meta-row"><span><b>SRE track</b></span><span>5 months</span><span class="achievement">$88k base</span></div>
              <div class="who"><div class="avatar" style="background:#0F4F46;">AS</div><div><div class="name">Aisha S.</div><div class="role">DevOps engineer &middot; gov, Victoria</div></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="testi">
              <div class="quote">Newcomer to Canada with foreign credentials nobody read. Yarova rebuilt my LinkedIn so recruiters found me in week three. The GitHub said senior; the title caught up.</div>
              <div class="meta-row"><span><b>DevOps track</b></span><span>9 months</span><span class="achievement">$96k base</span></div>
              <div class="who"><div class="avatar" style="background:#5B1B4F;">RN</div><div><div class="name">Ravi N.</div><div class="role">Cloud engineer &middot; enterprise, Mississauga</div></div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- PRICING -->
      <section id="pricing" class="section" data-screen-label="07 Pricing">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="sec-strip">
            <span class="num">06 / 07</span><span class="dot"></span><span>Pricing</span><span class="dot"></span><span>30 sec read</span>
          </div>
          <h2>One price.<br />No upsells. No subscription.</h2>

          <div class="price-wrap">
            <div class="price-card">
              <div class="label">DevOps &amp; SRE tracks &middot; September 2026</div>
              <h3>Yarova Simulated Work Experience</h3>
              <div class="price">
                <span class="num">$1,500</span>
                <span class="ccy">CAD</span>
              </div>
              <div class="when">One-time &middot; paid before day one</div>
              <div class="actions">
                <a href="https://cal.com/yarova-fxqeea/discovery-call" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-cal-link="yarova-fxqeea/discovery-call" data-cal-namespace="discovery-call" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}' class="btn btn-amber btn-lg">Book a discovery call <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
              </div>
              <div class="reverse">
                <b>Risk reversal</b>
                Complete the program and don&rsquo;t have an offer? Rejoin the next batch, free. Forever, until placed. Yarova carries the risk. You carry the work.
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="price-list">
              <h4>What&rsquo;s included</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>3-month squad placement (DevOps or SRE track)</li>
                <li>Daily standup with your squad &mdash; every weekday</li>
                <li>Team Lead async code review on every submission</li>
                <li>Real ticket board access (Jira-format tasks)</li>
                <li>Resume rebuilt from your actual ticket history</li>
                <li>Interview prep call before every interview you book</li>
                <li>Background check coordination &amp; documentation</li>
                <li>Day-1 onboarding prep call</li>
                <li>Probation check-in calls at 30, 60, and 90 days</li>
                <li>Re-enroll free in next batch if not placed</li>
              </ul>
              <h4 style="margin-top: 28px;">What&rsquo;s not included</h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="no">A guaranteed job or specific employer</li>
                <li class="no">Cloud-provider credits (~$50 over the program)</li>
                <li class="no">Placement outside Canada</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <section id="faq" class="section alt" data-screen-label="08 FAQ">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="sec-strip">
            <span class="num">07 / 07</span><span class="dot"></span><span>Questions</span><span class="dot"></span><span>Honest answers</span>
          </div>
          <h2>Questions you should ask<br /><em>before committing.</em></h2>

          <div class="faq">
            <details open>
              <summary><span>Do I need DevOps or SRE experience to join?</span><span class="glyph">−</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>You need basic Linux comfort: navigate the filesystem, run commands, read a man page without flinching. No prior DevOps or SRE title required. If you&rsquo;re not sure, the discovery call is the right place to find out &mdash; 30 minutes, no commitment.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>How long is one batch?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>Three months per track. DevOps and SRE run at different time slots so the same Team Lead covers both without conflict. New batches open every 3 months. If you miss the current batch, you go on the waitlist for the next one.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>What if I don&rsquo;t get a job after the batch ends?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>You re-enroll in the next batch, free. Then the one after, free. Until you have an offer. &ldquo;Complete the program&rdquo; is the operative condition &mdash; that means active standups, submitted tickets, and used support calls. This is a stay-until-it-works guarantee, not a refund-on-no-effort guarantee.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>Is the daily standup mandatory?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>Yes. This is the core of the model. Missing standups is the same as missing work at a real job. If life happens, you let your Team Lead know in advance &mdash; same as any real team. Consistent absenteeism means you exit the current batch and re-enroll in the next one.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary><span>Can I do this while working full-time?</span><span class="glyph">+</span></summary>
              <div class="answer"><p>Yes. The standup is one fixed daily slot &mdash; 15 minutes. Ticket work is async: you complete it in your own time. Plan on 8&ndash;12 hours per week outside the standup.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details>
